choices.text:
joining the European Union!

Yes but, in reality, after joining, our GDP hasn’t gone higher. The question is whether it’s really that worth it if after 20 yrs we haven’t seen any tangible benefits!

Already browsedThe Nordic countries are often juxtaposed towards each other, which is funny considering they faced each other in the military. I think mainly what distinguishes them is when you go there, it’s the differences you notice compared to the rest of Europe, i.e. how the laws are actually enforced. It feels constrained and strict, ready to judge your violation before you even break. Maybe it’s a more responsible version of the US?

The Ukip guy was also a bit weird in that he was trying to say they'll fix housing and make it so you can afford territorial stuff within the UK when basically London and most of the south east of England dominate everything else in terms of population and call the shots economically. That'll never happen. But at least it shows there's a huge economic rift in a once economically strong country in another European nation.

Finland is certainly in a better position to understand this situation as they used to ridem the same train as the UK, but fortunately they had already previously removed themselves from it.

I have to agree with the final straw commenter how silencing opposing views fails to help people reconsider and instead tries to cement their beliefs further. There’s a reason why.

And this is true, but then again he did make a good point
